                <h1>Easy Ways to Remove Wallpaper Glue</h1>
                <p>To effectively remove wallpaper glue, start by mixing hot water with a few drops of dish soap in a spray bottle. Spray the solution on the glue and let it sit for 15-20 minutes to soften the adhesive. Use a scraper or a sponge to gently lift the glue off the surface. Rinse the area with clean water and dry thoroughly.</p>
